{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JKYNV7xubEnquHkQj6mLH5","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll summarize the key findings for your migration task:\n\n1. Project Structure Overview:\n   - This is a Quarkus-based Java application\n   - Uses Maven for build management\n   - Implements a Real World API following Domain Driven Design (DDD) principles\n   - Structured in main packages: \n     * `application`: Web resources and models\n     * `domain`: Core business logic and models\n     * `infrastructure`: Implementation details\n\n2. Key Configuration Details:\n   - Java Version: 21\n   - Quarkus Version: 3.30.5\n   - Database: PostgreSQL\n   - Security: JWT-based authentication\n   - ORM: Hibernate with Panache\n   - Additional Libraries: \n     * Jackson for JSON processing\n     * Lombok for boilerplate reduction\n     * SmallRye for JWT and health checks\n\n3. Main Dependencies:\n   - Quarkus REST\n   - Hibernate Validator\n   - PostgreSQL JDBC\n   - JWT Authentication\n   - Jackson Data Binding\n\n4. Database Configuration (application.properties):\n   - PostgreSQL connection\n   - Database name: realworld\n   - Username/Password: realworld/realworld\n   - Hibernate set to drop-and-create database on startup\n\n5. Architectural Patterns:\n   - RESTful API design\n   - Feature-based domain logic\n   - Separate input/output models\n   - Transactional service methods\n   - Role-based access control\n\n6. Key Resources:\n   - Articles\n   - Users\n   - Profiles\n   - Comments\n   - Tags\n\n7. Authentication:\n   - Uses JWT tokens\n   - Roles: USER, ADMIN\n   - Token generation with public/private key pair\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the application for your migration task?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"b2d79342-4a25-4ce7-8a65-985f4cb4da9b"}
