{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Ws7HYudc9oB1mXzdBp7qYo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindCommentsByArticleSlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n     9→\n    10→@AllArgsConstructor\n    11→public class FindCommentsByArticleSlugImpl implements FindCommentsByArticleSlug {\n    12→\n    13→  private final FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    14→  private final CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    15→\n    16→  @Override\n    17→  public List<Comment> handle(String slug) {\n    18→    final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n    19→    return commentRepository.findCommentsByArticle(article);\n    20→  }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"59e80afe-b8bb-4a8c-a2ba-89169b4ff923"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MzMwaxzZgjf8EtG1sjMc3X","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateTag;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n     8→\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class CreateTagImpl implements CreateTag {\n    11→\n    12→  private final TagRepository tagRepository;\n    13→  private final TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public Tag handle(String name) {\n    17→    final var tag = tagBuilder.build(name);\n    18→    tagRepository.save(tag);\n    19→    return tag;\n    20→  }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"0ee8e121-828a-42e2-9265-929e9a9f8d43"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018DEn4GuLKJdy1EULeF23Tp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.UUID;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.ArticleFavoritesCount;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleById;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class ArticleFavoritesCountImpl implements ArticleFavoritesCount {\n    11→\n    12→  private final FindArticleById findArticleById;\n    13→  private final FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public long handle(UUID articleId) {\n    17→    final var article = findArticleById.handle(articleId);\n    18→    return favoriteRelationshipRepository.favoritesCount(article);\n    19→  }\n    20→}\n    21→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"e33d2038-8b08-4d06-8a72-eedba381d1df"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018YQoKdjxRNpgxtpLy8dd7Y","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateArticle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateSlugByTitle;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.*;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    11→\n    12→@AllArgsConstructor\n    13→public class CreateArticleImpl implements CreateArticle {\n    14→\n    15→  private final FindUserById findUserById;\n    16→  private final ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    17→  private final ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    18→  private final CreateSlugByTitle createSlugByTitle;\n    19→  private final FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists findTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists;\n    20→  private final TagRelationshipRepository tagRelationshipRepository;\n    21→\n    22→  @Override\n    23→  public Article handle(NewArticleInput newArticleInput) {\n    24→    final var author = findUserById.handle(newArticleInput.authorId());\n    25→    final var slug = createSlugByTitle.handle(newArticleInput.title());\n    26→    final var article =\n    27→        articleBuilder.build(\n    28→            slug,\n    29→            newArticleInput.title(),\n    30→            newArticleInput.description(),\n    31→            newArticleInput.body(),\n    32→            author);\n    33→    articleRepository.save(article);\n    34→    final var tags = findTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists.handle(newArticleInput.tagList());\n    35→    createTagRelationship(article, tags);\n    36→    return article;\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  private void createTagRelationship(Article article, List<Tag> tags) {\n    40→    tags.forEach(tag -> tagRelationshipRepository.save(new TagRelationship(article, tag)));\n    41→  }\n    42→}\n    43→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"9e71a9d1-d66d-4744-aed1-092d141787b5"}
