{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01K7RrcMYGG8jhCy9pq58BUo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.EmailAlreadyExistsException;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UsernameAlreadyExistsException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateUser;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.CreateUserInput;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    12→\n    13→@AllArgsConstructor\n    14→public class CreateUserImpl implements CreateUser {\n    15→\n    16→  private final UserRepository userRepository;\n    17→  private final HashProvider hashProvider;\n    18→  private final UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    19→\n    20→  @Override\n    21→  public User handle(CreateUserInput createUserInput) {\n    22→    final var user =\n    23→        userBuilder.build(\n    24→            createUserInput.getUsername(),\n    25→            createUserInput.getEmail(),\n    26→            createUserInput.getPassword());\n    27→    checkExistingUsername(user.getUsername());\n    28→    checkExistingEmail(user.getEmail());\n    29→    user.setPassword(hashProvider.hashPassword(user.getPassword()));\n    30→    userRepository.save(user);\n    31→    return user;\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  private void checkExistingUsername(String username) {\n    35→    if (userRepository.existsBy(\"username\", username)) {\n    36→      throw new UsernameAlreadyExistsException();\n    37→    }\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  private void checkExistingEmail(String email) {\n    41→    if (userRepository.existsBy(\"email\", email)) {\n    42→      throw new EmailAlreadyExistsException();\n    43→    }\n    44→  }\n    45→}\n    46→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"30e95b8d-bcea-4304-9f17-45ab60d912d9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JMFbGttEzp8ip1PZo7ir3K","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.UUID;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateSlugByTitle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     8→\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class CreateSlugByTitleImpl implements CreateSlugByTitle {\n    11→\n    12→  private final ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    13→  private final SlugProvider slugProvider;\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public String handle(String title) {\n    17→    String slug = slugProvider.slugify(title);\n    18→    if (articleRepository.existsBySlug(slug)) {\n    19→      slug += UUID.randomUUID().toString();\n    20→    }\n    21→    return slug;\n    22→  }\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"96ce179c-98bb-432b-92b5-b22a83d5cfce"}
