{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019q4BU3zuBQM8umVcZmDE6J","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.UUID;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfavoriteArticle;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class UnfavoriteArticleImpl implements UnfavoriteArticle {\n    11→\n    12→  private final FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    13→  private final FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public void handle(String articleSlug, UUID currentUserId) {\n    17→    final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(articleSlug);\n    18→    final var favoriteRelationshipOptional =\n    19→        favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), currentUserId);\n    20→    favoriteRelationshipOptional.ifPresent(favoriteRelationshipRepository::delete);\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"8f845b67-ff62-44fe-8a19-20f222816bda"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SCwdH1GboeySJxEHkUZvFy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.UUID;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserByUsername;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfollowUserByUsername;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n     9→\n    10→@AllArgsConstructor\n    11→public class UnfollowUserByUsernameImpl implements UnfollowUserByUsername {\n    12→\n    13→  private final FindUserById findUserById;\n    14→  private final FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    15→  private final FollowRelationshipRepository followRelationshipRepository;\n    16→\n    17→  @Override\n    18→  public void handle(UUID loggedUserId, String username) {\n    19→    final var loggedUser = findUserById.handle(loggedUserId);\n    20→    final var userToUnfollow = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    21→    final var followingRelationship =\n    22→        followRelationshipRepository.findByUsers(loggedUser, userToUnfollow).orElseThrow();\n    23→    followRelationshipRepository.remove(followingRelationship);\n    24→  }\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"f08d08e9-934e-4158-a8cd-7d9badd80987"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BKHDXFUfGuQm3YMnXmhgUN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.LinkedList;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateTag;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n    11→\n    12→@AllArgsConstructor\n    13→public class FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExistsImpl implements FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists {\n    14→\n    15→  private final TagRepository tagRepository;\n    16→  private final CreateTag createTag;\n    17→\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public List<Tag> handle(List<String> names) {\n    20→    final var tags = tagRepository.findByNames(names);\n    21→    tags.addAll(createTags(nonexistent(tags, names)));\n    22→    return tags;\n    23→  }\n    24→\n    25→  private List<Tag> createTags(List<String> names) {\n    26→    final var tags = new LinkedList<Tag>();\n    27→    names.forEach(name -> tags.add(createTag.handle(name)));\n    28→    return tags;\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  private List<String> nonexistent(List<Tag> existing, List<String> allNames) {\n    32→    return allNames.stream()\n    33→        .filter(name -> existing.stream().noneMatch(tag -> tag.getName().equalsIgnoreCase(name)))\n    34→        .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    35→  }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"f3e5dd0a-0808-4f40-944d-65b1d6241f57"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MF13XudTRf9Y41Ss5yUXFt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTags;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n     8→\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class FindTagsImpl implements FindTags {\n    11→\n    12→  private final TagRepository tagRepository;\n    13→\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public List<Tag> handle() {\n    16→    return tagRepository.findAllTags();\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"3cb3e47e-4668-4297-96e5-41afa2c4eb66"}
