{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HMav1iUSUtonNBVEnjxUZt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.UUID;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.IsArticleFavorited;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class IsArticleFavoritedImpl implements IsArticleFavorited {\n    11→\n    12→  private final FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    13→\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public boolean handle(Article article, UUID currentUserId) {\n    16→    return favoriteRelationshipRepository.isFavorited(article, currentUserId);\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"d326b64d-7648-40a3-9278-eda2bbe2e14b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011Y5jWPMwvXBpDW4BDwd7GV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.UUID;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.IsFollowingUser;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n     7→\n     8→@AllArgsConstructor\n     9→public class IsFollowingUserImpl implements IsFollowingUser {\n    10→\n    11→  private final FollowRelationshipRepository usersFollowedRepository;\n    12→\n    13→  @Override\n    14→  public boolean handle(UUID currentUserId, UUID followedUserId) {\n    15→    return usersFollowedRepository.isFollowing(currentUserId, followedUserId);\n    16→  }\n    17→}\n    18→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QjGCvr1c1AhMy6rkGfhwSL","session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"58b8b8c9-0db4-47f3-a58d-755ee200d34d"}
