{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012KfdF9JWXxr5ZXdW7kSuCz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All 6 files have been successfully written for the Spring Boot migration of the Quarkus RealWorld API application. Here's a summary of what was created:\n\n## Files Created/Updated:\n\n### 1. **RealWorldApiApplication.java**\n- Location: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/RealWorldApiApplication.java`\n- Main Spring Boot application entry point with `@SpringBootApplication` annotation\n\n### 2. **JwtTokenProvider.java**\n- Location: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/JwtTokenProvider.java`\n- Replaces Quarkus SmallRye JWT with Spring-compatible JWT implementation using jjwt library\n- Loads RSA keys from classpath (privateKey.pem and publicKey.pem)\n- Provides methods for creating, validating, and extracting subjects from JWT tokens\n- Uses RS256 signing algorithm with 24-hour token expiration\n\n### 3. **JwtAuthenticationFilter.java**\n- Location: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/JwtAuthenticationFilter.java`\n- Spring Security filter that intercepts requests and validates JWT tokens\n- Extracts tokens from \"Token\" or \"Bearer\" authorization headers\n- Sets authentication in SecurityContext for authenticated requests\n\n### 4. **SecurityConfig.java**\n- Location: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/SecurityConfig.java`\n- Configures Spring Security with stateless session management\n- Defines public endpoints (user registration, login, article/profile viewing)\n- Protects authenticated endpoints (user profile updates, article creation/modification, favorites, follows)\n- Disables CSRF for REST API\n- Adds JWT filter before standard authentication filter\n\n### 5. **BCryptHashProvider.java**\n- Location: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/BCryptHashProvider.java`\n- Replaces Quarkus Elytron BcryptUtil with Spring Security's BCryptPasswordEncoder\n- Implements HashProvider interface for password hashing and verification\n\n### 6. **SlugifySlugProvider.java**\n- Location: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/SlugifySlugProvider.java`\n- Updated from Quarkus `@ApplicationScoped` to Spring `@Component`\n- Implements SlugProvider interface using the Slugify library\n\n## Key Migration Changes:\n\n1. **Dependency Injection**: Changed from Jakarta CDI (`@ApplicationScoped`) to Spring (`@Component`, `@Configuration`)\n2. **JWT Handling**: Migrated from SmallRye JWT to jjwt library with explicit key loading\n3. **Security**: Migrated from JAX-RS security annotations to Spring Security filter chain\n4. **Password Hashing**: Changed from Quarkus Elytron to Spring Security BCrypt\n5. **Configuration**: Uses Spring `@Value` annotations for externalized configuration\n\nThese files provide the core Spring Boot infrastructure needed for the RealWorld API migration, maintaining the same functionality as the original Quarkus application while using Spring Boot conventions and libraries."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77854f62-3341-42f0-ba47-aba7925f4b32","uuid":"cf24a55f-e0ee-4fa7-9ad8-761115b0851e"}
