{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TAGzVNQriWsikqEGFmBKBi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonFormat;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     5→import io.quarkus.runtime.annotations.RegisterForReflection;\n     6→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     7→import java.util.UUID;\n     8→import lombok.Getter;\n     9→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n    10→import lombok.Setter;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    12→\n    13→@Getter\n    14→@Setter\n    15→@NoArgsConstructor\n    16→@JsonRootName(\"comment\")\n    17→@RegisterForReflection\n    18→public class CommentResponse {\n    19→\n    20→  private UUID id;\n    21→\n    22→  @JsonFormat(shape = JsonFormat.Shape.STRING, pattern = \"yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'Z'\")\n    23→  private LocalDateTime createdAt;\n    24→\n    25→  @JsonFormat(shape = JsonFormat.Shape.STRING, pattern = \"yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'Z'\")\n    26→  private LocalDateTime updatedAt;\n    27→\n    28→  private String body;\n    29→  private ProfileResponse author;\n    30→\n    31→  public CommentResponse(Comment comment, ProfileResponse author) {\n    32→    this.id = comment.getId();\n    33→    this.createdAt = comment.getCreatedAt();\n    34→    this.updatedAt = comment.getUpdatedAt();\n    35→    this.body = comment.getBody();\n    36→    this.author = author;\n    37→  }\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X2xK2TdkPMxMKJwrdZXJv9","session_id